Class PUZPuzzleOutputStream

All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Closeable, java.io.Flushable
public class PUZPuzzleOutputStream
extends PuzzleOutputStream<PUZPuzzle>

Provides an OutputStream for deserializing a PUZ image into a PUZPuzzle object.

The strict property of this class controls how strictly the checksums in the PUZ file image are checked prior to deserialization. If the strict property is true (the default value), then checksums for the PUZ image are computed and compared against the checksums stored in the image; if the checksums do not match, an IOException is thrown. If the strict property is false, the checksums are not validated prior to deserialization.

Two individual puzzles produced by this class will be equal as long as they are logically equivalent. If the puzzles have an equal grid, solution, player state, clues, and other descriptive properties, then the puzzles will be equal even if some details of their file representations vary (such as the order of extra sections or the numbering of rebus entries).

Author:
Eric Peterson

toPuzzle

public PUZPuzzle toPuzzle()
                   throws java.io.IOException
Deserializes the PUZ image written into this input stream into a PUZPuzzle object. If the strict property of this class is true, then checksum validation is performed. If the solution in the PUZ image is encrypted, the unlock code is found and the solution is decrypted automatically.

Specified by:
toPuzzle in class PuzzleOutputStream<PUZPuzzle>
Returns:
The deserialized PUZPuzzle object
Throws:
java.io.IOException - An exception occurred during deserialization. This can happen if an inconsistency in the PUZ image is detected or if the strict property is true and the computed checksums of the PUZ image do not match the checksums stored in the PUZ image.
